This paper deals with the multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) communication channel and its equalization scheme, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. It also involves the use of precoding matrices, which is a common technique in networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of linear codes, which is relevant to coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper applies the results to closed-loop multicast, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
